18 of the Ten Commandments on public property may have "multiple purposes"
19 such as "historical significance as one of the foundations of our legal system"
20 and represents a "common cultural heritage". Id. at 54.
21 (8) The Mayflower Compact of 1620 was America's first written
22 constitution and made a Covenant with Almighty God to "form a civil body
23 politic". This was the first purely American document of self-government and
24 affirmed the link between civil society and God.
25 (9) The Declaration of Independence, adopted by Congress on July 4,
26 1776, provides that "(we) hold these truths to be self-evident, that all men are
27 created equal, that they are endowed by their Creator with certain unalienable
28 Rights, that among these are Life, Liberty and the pursuit of Happiness".
29 (10) The Northwest Ordinance of 1787 provided a method of admitting
30 new states to the Union from the territory as the country expanded to the
