4 J.(1) The commissioner of administration shall permit and arrange for
5 the placement on the Louisiana State Capitol grounds of a suitable monument
6 displaying the Ten Commandments. The commissioner shall designate the
7 location of the monument, which shall be among other monuments, and shall
8 oversee its installation. The design, construction, placement, and maintenance
9 of the monument shall be free of charge to the state. The commissioner may
10 delegate his responsibilities provided in this Subsection to the office of state
11 buildings.
12 (2) The commissioner shall accept and consider proposals for the
13 monument from private entities and shall select the proposal for the monument
14 that will be installed. In selecting a proposal, the commissioner shall consider
15 the appropriateness of the proposed design, the demonstrated ability of the
16 responsible entity to pay the cost of design, construction, installation, and
17 maintenance of the monument, and any other factor he deems appropriate. The
18 commissioner shall make such selection by December 31, 2026; however, if he
19 has not received an acceptable proposal by that date, he shall select the first
20 acceptable proposal he receives after that date.
21 (3)(a) The overall dimensions of the monument shall not exceed six feet
22 in height, four feet in width, and four feet in depth, including any base on which
23 the monument sits.
24 (b) The monument shall use the same text provided in R.S. 25:1282,
25 which is the same text that was used in Van Orden v. Perry, 545 U.S. 677 (2005),
26 that was ruled constitutional by the Supreme Court of the United States.
27 (c) The monument shall include a plaque that includes the text of the
28 "Context for Acknowledging America's Religious History as Culture, Tradition,
29 and the History of Law" as set forth in R.S. 25:1283.
